research_municipality_step.notes: Woodbridge Township, NJ operates under a Mayor-Council system of government as per the Faulkner Act. The Mayor and nine Council members are elected to four-year terms. The Council consists of four at-large members and five members representing specific wards. There was a slight discrepancy in the specific 'Council President' and 'Council Vice President' roles between different sources; the official Woodbridge Township website's Council page was prioritized for these roles.
